{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:985-992`, `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1062-1088`, `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:412-419`, and `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1530-1536` still only kill/reap the direct child PID. The command is spawned without its own process group/job object, and the timeout path only calls `send_sigkill()`/`Child::kill()` on that one child before declaring teardown confirmed. If the backend shells out or backgrounds a helper that inherits stdout/stderr, the parent can exit while the descendant keeps running; the invocation is reported as timed out/retryable, but the leaked descendant survives into the next retry. That misses the acceptance criterion that hanging backend processes are killed after timeout.","rationale":"The new hard-timeout path is not actually robust against common process-tree hangs, so retries can stack on top of orphaned backend helpers."},{"body":"`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1064-1088` drops the invocation from `active_children` and returns immediately when timeout teardown is not confirmed, but unlike `cancel()` there is no background reap fallback. The existing cancel path explicitly keeps reaping in the background at `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1380-1390` via `spawn_background_reap()` (`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1520-1525`); the timeout path does not. A slow-to-die child can therefore outlive tracking and subsequent retries/cancellations will no longer be able to find it.","rationale":"Even without descendant processes, the unconfirmed-timeout branch can leave a still-live child running after the adapter has forgotten it."},{"body":"Timeout-like failures that come back as `TransportFailure` lose their diagnostics. The timeout branch intentionally downgrades unconfirmed teardown to `TransportFailure` at `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1068-1075`, but `invoke()` only preserves failed artifacts when `error.failure_class() == Timeout` and otherwise calls `prepared.cleanup()` at `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1259-1266` (same pattern in the stale-session retry path at `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1298-1308`). That deletes the schema/last-message temp files for the hardest timeout failures to debug.","rationale":"This is a significant operability gap in the exact failure mode where operators most need preserved artifacts."}],"summary":"Git diff was empty in the worktree, so I reviewed the committed HEAD changes for the retry-policy task in `process_backend.rs`, `retry_policy.rs`, and the workflow engine, and ran `cargo test --test unit` plus focused library tests. The retry-budget/backoff/resume changes look coherent overall, but the new process-backend timeout path still has cleanup gaps around child-process teardown and diagnostics."}